liY~N A^abadiY~N", "text_ar": "اَزَلِىٌّ اَبَدِىٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "existing from eternity,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and consequently"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "existing to eternity"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; and this is God [who is also called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alqadiymu AlA^azaliY~u", "text_ar": "القَدِيمُ الاَزَلِىُّ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the Ancient without beginning"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA A^azaliY~N wa laA A^abadiY~N", "text_ar": "لَا اَزَلِىٌّ وَ لَا اَبَدِىٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "not existing from eternity nor existing to eternity"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; and such is the present world: and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^abadiY~N", "text_ar": "اَبَدِىٌّ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gayoru A^azaliY~", "text_ar": "غَيْرُ اَزَلِىّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "existing to eternity without existing from eternity"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; and such is the world to come; the reverse of which [last] is impossible: (TA:) it is a rel. n. from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^azalN", "text_ar": "اَزَلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": or, accord. to some, it is not [genuine] Arabic: (TA:) or it is originally"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yazaliY~N", "text_ar": "يَزَلِىٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", a rel. n. from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lamo yazalo", "text_ar": "لَمْ يَزَلْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, K,) a phrase applied to that which is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qadiym", "text_ar": "قَدِيم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and is formed by contraction; (S;) then, the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Y", "text_ar": "ى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is changed into"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A", "text_ar": "ا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as being easier of pronunciation; as in"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^azaniY~N", "text_ar": "اَزَنِىٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", applied to a spear, in relation to"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*uw yazan", "text_ar": "ذُو يَزَن"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (S, K,* Sgh, TA;) and as in"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^avorabiY~N", "text_ar": "اَثْرَبِىٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", applied to a blade, (S, Sgh, TA,) in relation to"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yavorib", "text_ar": "يَثْرِب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (TA:) so say some of the learned. (S.)"}], "source_refs": ["TA", "S", "K", "Sgh"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}